{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1769470814,"nonce":"7xoUBx7WyChTnNwmEphOCTDx/Pw=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87l9p83zwAAAAUxWxuo"},"added":["bug"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1769471562,"nonce":"ZFDTxbYgIImR2I1oSG2o7PXI71o=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87iovoo","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/49#issuecomment-3802331688"},"message":"## Agent Assessment: Critical Architecture Issue\n\n**Severity**: 🔥 CRITICAL  \n**Status**: Requires immediate attention before Issue #46 can proceed  \n**Analysis Date**: 2026-01-26\n\n### Problem Confirmed\nThis is a fundamental design flaw in the identity system:\n\n- **Current approach** (persistent `.git/config`): Works for containerized agents (Antigravity) but breaks shared workspaces\n- **Impact**: Host-based agents (Copilot CLI, Gemini CLI) must choose between:\n  - Running the script → disrupts user's workflow\n  - Skipping the script → violates identity policy (commits as user)\n- **Result**: Architecture requirement in `AI_IDENTITY_STRATEGY.md` cannot be met for CLI agents\n\n### Root Cause\nGit config priority: Environment variables \u003e .git/config \u003e global config\n\nCurrent script uses only .git/config (persistent), which conflicts with shared workspace usage.\n\n### Recommended Solution: Two-Tier Approach\n\n**1. Ephemeral Identity (NEW - for host-based agents)**\n- Create `.agent/scripts/set_git_identity_env.sh`\n- Export GIT_AUTHOR_NAME, GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL, GIT_COMMITTER_NAME, GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL\n- Session-only (temp shell vars, not persistent)\n- Doesn't touch .git/config\n- User's config untouched\n- Works for shared workspaces\n\n**2. Persistent Identity (KEEP - for containerized agents)**\n- Keep existing `configure_git_identity.sh` unchanged\n- Update docs to clarify when to use each approach\n- Use in isolated environments (Antigravity, dedicated machines)\n\n**3. Auto-Detection (FUTURE ENHANCEMENT)**\n- Detect if running in container vs. host\n- Choose correct method automatically\n- Update onboarding to recommend appropriate approach\n\n### Implementation Phases\n\n**Phase 1 (URGENT - 1-2 hours)**\n- Create `.agent/scripts/set_git_identity_env.sh`\n- Update `AGENT_ONBOARDING.md` with ephemeral approach for host-based agents\n- Update `AI_IDENTITY_STRATEGY.md` to document both options\n- Add decision tree: when to use each approach\n\n**Phase 2 (Enhancement)**\n- Create `.agent/scripts/detect_agent_environment.sh` for auto-detection\n- Update workflows to auto-select appropriate method\n- Test with both Copilot CLI and containerized agents\n\n**Phase 3 (Documentation)**\n- Update `COPILOT_CLI_QUICK_START.md` (from Issue #46) with correct approach\n- Add examples for common scenarios\n- Document testing procedure for verification\n\n### Blockers \u0026 Dependencies\n\nThis issue **blocks** Issue #46 (Copilot CLI Quick Start) because the current onboarding is broken for host-based agents.\n\n### Critical Insight\n\nI ran `configure_git_identity.sh` in this session, which is why PR #47 shows correct attribution. However, if the user commits afterward in the same workspace, they'd need to manually revert the .git/config. This explains why host-based agents might skip the identity setup—it's disruptive to shared workspace usage.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- Host-based agents can set ephemeral identity without modifying shared .git/config\n- Persistent approach still works for containerized agents\n- Documentation clearly explains both options\n- Verified with actual Copilot CLI and Gemini CLI sessions\n- Integration with Issue #46 (Quick Start docs)","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1769471953,"nonce":"8nuC61laS6/lyvUE9v9UeTkox+M=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87io0uP","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/49#issuecomment-3802352527"},"message":"So far, I, the user, have used separate checkouts of the repo for copilot cli, gemini cli, antigravity, and my own coding. This is to prevent agents from different frameworks from stepping on each others toes as I learn all of this. Moving forward, if I'm to start using one checkout for all my agent and self work, this will need to be properly sorted out.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1769531372,"nonce":"zWXb21kgY7boJadxahDH58JwAs0=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87l9p83zwAAAAUyiw3T"},"status":2}]}